Maintaining a current row and a direction flag. Whenever I reach the first or last row, I reverse direction. 
I store characters in row-wise StringBuilders and finally concatenate them.
numRows = 1 → return original string. numRows >= s.length() → return original string


class Solution {
    public String convert(String s, int numRows) {
        if (numRows == 1 || s.length() <= numRows) {
            return s;
        }
        StringBuilder[] rows = new StringBuilder[numRows];
        for (int i = 0; i < numRows; i++) {
            rows[i] = new StringBuilder();
        }
        int curr = 0;
        boolean down = false;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            rows[curr].append(c);
            if (curr == 0 || curr == numRows - 1) {
                down = !down;
            }
            curr += down ? 1 : -1;
        }
        StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();
        for (StringBuilder r : rows) {
            ans.append(r);
        }
        return ans.toString();
    }
}
